            <scopecontent id="aspace_18eac307d49dc10eb686056cc9df9a80">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Pierson Family Papers contain three items; notes of Margaret H. Pierson on her reading at Vassar, a notebook on sewing kept by Louise R. Pierson at Pratt Institute, and the diary of Laura Pierson's European trip in 1926. The Vassar notebook simply lists Margaret's readings, the Pratt Institute notebook contains fabric samples in addition to the notes, and Laura's European diary contains her impressions of her travels.</p>
            </scopecontent>
